Øresund Bridge.label: Øresund Bridge
Øresund Bridge.description: The Öresund or Øresund Bridge is a double-track railway and dual carriageway bridge-tunnel across the Øresund strait between Scania and Denmark. Wikipedia

17-Mile Drive.label: 17-Mile Drive

A1 (Bosnia and Herzegovina).description: The A1 motorway is a motorway in Bosnia and Herzegovina that is part of the Corridor Vc and, together with two Croatian motorways and the Hungarian M6, will provide a modern and fast road connection ... Wikipedia

A1 autostrada (Poland).label: A1 autostrada

A1 (Croatia).label: A1
A1 (Croatia).description: The A1 motorway is the longest motorway in Croatia, spanning 465.5 kilometers. As it connects Zagreb, the nation's capital, to Split, the second largest city in the country and the largest city in ... Wikipedia

A1 motorway (Netherlands).label: A1 motorway
A1 motorway (Netherlands).description: The A1 is a motorway in the Netherlands. The road connects the city of Amsterdam, near the interchange Watergraafsmeer, with the German border, near Oldenzaal and Bad Bentheim, and the German Autobahn BAB 30. Wikipedia

A2 motorway (Switzerland).label: A2 motorway
A2 motorway (Switzerland).description: The A2 is a motorway in Switzerland. It forms Switzerland's main north-south axis from Basel to Chiasso, meandering with a slight drift toward the east. Wikipedia

A5 (Croatia).label: A5
A5 (Croatia).description: The A5 motorway is a motorway in Croatia spanning 55.5 kilometres. It connects Osijek, the largest city in Slavonia region, to the Croatian motorway network at the Sredanci interchange of the A3 motorway. Wikipedia

A6 motorway (Switzerland).label: A6 motorway
A6 motorway (Switzerland).description: The A6 motorway, an Autobahn in Switzerland, connects Biel / Bienne over Bern with Thun. The A6 is located entirely within the Canton of Berne and, in particular, has a great regional significance, so ... Wikipedia

A9 (Croatia).label: A9
A9 (Croatia).description: The A9 motorway is a north–south motorway in Croatia, with a length of 78.3 kilometres. Beginning in Pula, the largest city on the Istrian peninsula, it runs north to the Croatian motorway and expressway network at the Kanfanar interchange. Wikipedia

Adolphe Bridge.label: Adolphe Bridge
Adolphe Bridge.description: Adolphe Bridge is an arch bridge in Luxembourg City, in southern Luxembourg. The bridge takes road traffic across the Pétrusse, connecting Boulevard Royal, in Ville Haute, to Avenue de la Liberté, in Gare. Wikipedia

Arbatsko-Pokrovskaya Line.label: Arbatsko-Pokrovskaya Line
Arbatsko-Pokrovskaya Line.description: The Arbatsko–Pokrovskaya Line is one of the lines of the Moscow Metro. Chronologically the second to open, it connects the district of Mitino and the town of Krasnogorsk to the northwest of Moscow with ... Wikipedia

Autostrada A18 (Italy).label: Autostrada A18
Autostrada A18 (Italy).description: The Autostrada A18 is a 77 km motorway on the Ionian coast of Sicily that links Messina to Catania. The motorway is linked to the A20 Messina-Palermo at its northern-end and to the A19 Palermo-Catania ... Wikipedia

Autostrada A19 (Italy).label: Autostrada A19
Autostrada A19 (Italy).description: The Autostrada A19 is a 199 km motorway on the island of Sicily that links Palermo to Catania. The motorway from Palermo follows the Tyrrhenian coast esatwards for 46 km and then turns south to go over ... Wikipedia

Autostrada A26 (Italy).label: Autostrada A26
Autostrada A26 (Italy).description: The Autostrada A26 is a motorway in the northwestern Italian regions of Liguria and Piedmont. It is named the Autostrada dei Trafori after the numerous tunnels through which it passes, both Apennine and Subalpine. Wikipedia

Baku Metro.label: Baku Metro
Baku Metro.description: Baku Metro is a rapid transit system serving Baku, the capital of Azerbaijan. First opened on November 6, 1967, during the time of the Soviet Union, it has the features found in most other ex-Soviet ... Wikipedia

Berlin S-Bahn.label: Berlin S-Bahn
Berlin S-Bahn.description: The Berlin S-Bahn is a rapid transit railway system in and around Berlin, the capital city of Germany. Wikipedia

Birdsville Track.label: Birdsville Track
Birdsville Track.description: The Birdsville Track is a notable outback road in Australia. The 517 km track runs from Marree, a small town in northern South Australia, north across the Tirari Desert and Sturt Stony Desert, ending in Birdsville in south western Queensland. Wikipedia

Cannon Street Railway Bridge.label: Cannon Street Railway Bridge
Cannon Street Railway Bridge.description: Cannon Street Railway Bridge is a bridge in central London, crossing the River Thames. Downstream, the next bridge is London Bridge, and upstream Southwark Bridge. It carries trains over the river to Cannon Street station on the north bank. Wikipedia

Centennial Bridge, Panama.label: Centennial Bridge, Panama
Centennial Bridge, Panama.description: Panama's Centennial Bridge is a major bridge crossing the Panama Canal. It was built to supplement the overcrowded Bridge of the Americas and to replace it as the carrier of the Pan-American Highway. Wikipedia

Chūō Main Line.label: Chūō Main Line
Chūō Main Line.description: The Chūō Main Line, commonly called the Chūō Line, is one of the major trunk railway lines in Japan. Wikipedia

Carnaby Street.label: Carnaby Street
Carnaby Street.description: Carnaby Street is a pedestrianised shopping street in the City of Westminster, London, located in the Soho district, near Oxford Street and Regent Street. Wikipedia

Chelsea Bridge.label: Chelsea Bridge
Chelsea Bridge.description: Chelsea Bridge is a bridge over the River Thames in west London, connecting Chelsea on the north bank to Battersea on the south bank. There have been two Chelsea Bridges, on the site of what was an ancient ford. Wikipedia

Chemins de fer du Jura.label: Chemins de fer du Jura
Chemins de fer du Jura.description: The Chemins de fer du Jura, the railways of the Jura canton in northern Switzerland, came about as the result of an amalgamation, in 1944, of four independent companies connecting Porrentruy to Bonfol, ... Wikipedia

Colemanville Covered Bridge.label: Colemanville Covered Bridge
Colemanville Covered Bridge.description: The Colemanville Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Pequea Creek in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. After Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge, it is Lancaster County's second-longest single-span covered bridge still being used. Wikipedia

Church Street, Monmouth.label: Church Street, Monmouth
Church Street, Monmouth.description: Church Street is a pedestrianised street in the centre of Monmouth, Wales. It now contains a variety of independent shops, restaurants, commercial art galleries, and the Savoy Theatre. Wikipedia

D4 motorway (Slovakia).label: D4 motorway
D4 motorway (Slovakia).description: D4 is a motorway in southwestern Slovakia. The planned highway is commonly referred to as the Bratislava bypass. Currently there is only a short stretch from Austrian border at Jarovce to the junction with D2, opened in 1998. Wikipedia

D1 motorway (Czech Republic).label: D1 motorway
D1 motorway (Czech Republic).description: D1 motorway is the main highway of the Czech Republic. Currently it connects the two biggest Czech cities, Prague and Brno, in the future it will link Ostrava and to the Czech-Polish border in Věřňovice / Gorzyczki. Wikipedia

Fehmarn Sound Bridge.label: Fehmarn Sound Bridge
Fehmarn Sound Bridge.description: The Fehmarn Sound Bridge connects the German island of Fehmarn in the Baltic Sea with the German mainland near Großenbrode. Wikipedia

D5 motorway (Czech Republic).label: D5 motorway
D5 motorway (Czech Republic).description: D5 motorway is a highway in the Czech Republic. It runs from Prague through Pilsen into Germany. D5 is 151 km long; a bypass of Pilsen includes the 380 metre long Valík Tunnel and the 445 metre long bridge over the River Úhlava. Wikipedia

East Coast Main Line.label: East Coast Main Line
East Coast Main Line.description: The East Coast Main Line is a 393-mile long high-speed railway link between London, Peterborough, Doncaster, Wakefield, Leeds, York, Darlington, Newcastle, Edinburgh and is electrified along the whole route. Wikipedia

Dorfbahn Serfaus.label: Dorfbahn Serfaus
Dorfbahn Serfaus.description: The Dorfbahn Serfaus is an unusual underground air cushion funicular transit system in the Tyrolian village of Serfaus in Austria. The name literally translates as Serfaus Village Railway. Wikipedia

FirstGroup.label: FirstGroup
FirstGroup.description: FirstGroup is a British transport group, registered and operating in the United Kingdom. The company also operate transport services in Ireland, Denmark, Canada and the United States. Wikipedia

Fosse Way.label: Fosse Way
Fosse Way.description: The Fosse Way was a Roman road in England that linked Exeter in South West England to Lincoln in Lincolnshire, via Ilchester, Bath, Cirencester and Leicester. Wikipedia

Genoa Metro.label: Genoa Metro
Genoa Metro.description: The Genoa Metro is a light metro consisting of a single line that connects the centre of Genoa, Italy with the suburb of Rivarolo Ligure, to the north-west of the city centre. Wikipedia

Grosvenor Bridge.label: Grosvenor Bridge
Grosvenor Bridge.description: Grosvenor Bridge, originally known as, and alternatively called Victoria Railway Bridge, is a railway bridge over the River Thames in London, between Vauxhall Bridge and Chelsea Bridge. Wikipedia

Gotthard Base Tunnel.label: Gotthard Base Tunnel
Gotthard Base Tunnel.description: The Gotthard Base Tunnel is a railway tunnel in the heart of the Swiss Alps expected to open in 2016. Wikipedia

Hörn Bridge.label: Hörn Bridge
Hörn Bridge.description: The Hörn Bridge is a folding bridge in the city of Kiel in the German state of Schleswig-Holstein. The bridge spans over the end of the Kiel Fjord and was designed by Gerkan, Marg and Partners. Wikipedia

Great River Road.label: Great River Road
Great River Road.description: The Great River Road is a collection of state and local roads which follow the course of the Mississippi River through ten states of the United States. Wikipedia

Hangzhou Bay Bridge.label: Hangzhou Bay Bridge
Hangzhou Bay Bridge.description: Hangzhou Bay Bridge is a highway bridge with a cable-stayed portion across Hangzhou Bay in the eastern coastal region of China. It connects the municipalities of Jiaxing and Ningbo in Zhejiang province. Wikipedia

Herr's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Herr's Mill Covered Bridge
Herr's Mill Covered Bridge.description:
The Herr's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Pequea Creek in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. It is also sometimes known as Soudersburg Bridge.
The bridge has a double span, wooden, double Burr arch trusses design. Wikipedia

Greyhound Lines.label: Greyhound Lines
Greyhound Lines.description: Greyhound Lines, Inc., called Greyhound for short, is an intercity bus service common carrier serving over 3,700 destinations in the United States, Canada, and Mexico. Wikipedia

Great Ocean Road.label: Great Ocean Road
Great Ocean Road.description: The Great Ocean Road is an Australian National Heritage listed 243 kilometres stretch of road along the south-eastern coast of Australia between the Victorian cities of Torquay and Allansford. Wikipedia

Hamburg S-Bahn.label: Hamburg S-Bahn
Hamburg S-Bahn.description: The Hamburg S-Bahn is rapid mass transit railway network in the Hamburg Metropolitan Region. Together, the S-Bahn, the Hamburg U-Bahn, the AKN railway and the regional railway form the backbone of ... Wikipedia

Highway 1 (Israel).label: Highway 1
Highway 1 (Israel).description: Highway 1, is the main highway connecting Tel Aviv and Jerusalem in Israel. Wikipedia

Highway 2 (Israel).label: Highway 2
Highway 2 (Israel).description: Highway 2 is an Israeli highway located on the coastal plain of the Mediterranean Sea. It begins a major arterial road within Tel Aviv, becoming a freeway as it exits the city northward continuing to Haifa. Wikipedia

Highway 4 (Israel).label: Highway 4
Highway 4 (Israel).description: Highway 4 is an Israeli highway that runs along Israel's entire coastal plain of the Mediterranean Sea, its route in the north runs from the Rosh HaNikra border crossing with Lebanon until the Erez Border Crossing with the Gaza Strip. Wikipedia

Highway 3 (Israel).label: Highway 3
Highway 3 (Israel).description: Highway 3 is a highway in Israel. It begins at Highway 4 on the outskirts of Ashkelon, running east-northeast, passing through Kiryat Malakhi and Latrun, and ending just short of Modi'in. Wikipedia

Hohenzollern Bridge.label: Hohenzollern Bridge
Hohenzollern Bridge.description: The Hohenzollern Bridge is a bridge crossing the river Rhine in the German city of Cologne. It crosses the Rhine at kilometre 688.5. Wikipedia

Highway 6 (Israel).label: Highway 6
Highway 6 (Israel).description: Highway 6, also known as the Trans-Israel Highway, is a major electronic toll highway in Israel.Highway 6 is the first Israeli Build-Operate-Transfer road constructed, carried out mainly by the private ... Wikipedia

Highway 5 (Israel).label: Highway 5
Highway 5 (Israel).description: Highway 5, or the Trans-Samaria Highway, is one of Israel's main highways, connecting the Mediterranean coast immediately north of Tel Aviv with the central Sharon plain and eastwards to Ariel and other ... Wikipedia

Interstate Bridge.label: Interstate Bridge
Interstate Bridge.description: The Interstate Bridge is a pair of nearly identical steel vertical-lift, "Parker type" through-truss bridges that carry Interstate 5 traffic over the Columbia River between Vancouver, Washington and Portland, Oregon in the United States. Wikipedia

Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge
Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge located in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. The bridge has a single span, wooden, double Burr arch trusses design. Wikipedia

Ho Chi Minh City Metro.label: Ho Chi Minh City Metro
Ho Chi Minh City Metro.description: The Ho Chi Minh City Metro is a proposed rapid transit network that will serve Ho Chi Minh City in Vietnam. Wikipedia

Icefields Parkway.label: Icefields Parkway
Icefields Parkway.description: The Icefields Parkway, also known as Highway 93 north, is a scenic road in Alberta, Canada. It parallels the Continental Divide, traversing the rugged landscape of the Canadian Rockies, travelling ... Wikipedia

Interstate 238.label: Interstate 238
Interstate 238.description: Interstate 238 is a short auxiliary route of the Interstate Highway System in the San Francisco Bay Area in the U.S. state of California. Wikipedia

Interstate 5 in Washington.label: Interstate 5 in Washington
Interstate 5 in Washington.description: Interstate 5 in Washington is a 276.62-mile highway in the U.S. state of Washington that extends from its border with Oregon to its border with Canada. Wikipedia

Jack Pesch Bridge.label: Jack Pesch Bridge
Jack Pesch Bridge.description: The Jack Pesch Bridge is a bridge for pedestrians and cyclists which crosses the Brisbane River. The bridge is named in honour of Jack Pesch, a cycling champion during the 1930s. Wikipedia

Interstate H-1.label: Interstate H-1
Interstate H-1.description: Interstate H-1 is the busiest Interstate Highway in Hawaii, United States, located on the island of O‘ahu. Despite the number, this is an east–west highway—the 'H'-series numbering reflects the order in which routes were funded and built. Wikipedia

Japanese National Railways.label: Japanese National Railways
Japanese National Railways.description: Japanese National Railways, abbreviated Kokutetsu or "JNR", was the body which operated the national railway network of Japan from 1949 to 1987. Wikipedia

Karni crossing.label: Karni crossing
Karni crossing.description: The Karni Crossing was a cargo terminal on the Israel-Gaza Strip barrier. It is located in the north-eastern end of the Gaza Strip and was opened in 1994 after the signing of the Oslo Accords, in order ... Wikipedia

Keller's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Keller's Covered Bridge
Keller's Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Keller's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Cocalico Creek in Ephrata Township, Lancaster County in the US state of Pennsylvania. A county-owned and maintained bridge, its official designation is the Cocalico No. 5 Bridge. Wikipedia

Interstate H-3.label: Interstate H-3
Interstate H-3.description: Interstate H-3 is an intrastate Interstate Highway located on the island of O'ahu in the state of Hawai'i in the United States. H-3 is also known as the John A. Burns Freeway. Wikipedia

Interstate H-2.label: Interstate H-2
Interstate H-2.description: Interstate H-2 is an intrastate Interstate Highway located on the island of O‘ahu in Hawai‘i, USA. H-2 is also known as the Veterans Memorial Freeway. Wikipedia

Krk Bridge.label: Krk Bridge
Krk Bridge.description: Krk Bridge is a 1430 m long reinforced concrete arch bridge connecting the Croatian island of Krk to the mainland and carrying over a million vehicles per year. Wikipedia

Krka Bridge.label: Krka Bridge
Krka Bridge.description: The Krka Bridge is located in Croatia, between the Skradin and Šibenik interchanges. It is a 391 metres long concrete arch bridge spanning the Krka River at a height of 65 metres. Wikipedia

Kaluzhsko-Rizhskaya Line.label: Kaluzhsko-Rizhskaya Line
Kaluzhsko-Rizhskaya Line.description: The Kaluzhsko–Rizhskaya Line is a line of the Moscow Metro, that originally existed as two separate radial lines, Rizhskaya and Kaluzhskaya opened in 1958 and 1962, respectively. Wikipedia

Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge
Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Mill Creek in the Lancaster County Park in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. Wikipedia

Kobe Municipal Subway.label: Kobe Municipal Subway
Kobe Municipal Subway.description: Kobe Municipal Subway is the subway of Kobe. It has two lines. Wikipedia

Landis Mill Covered Bridge.label: Landis Mill Covered Bridge
Landis Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Landis Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans the Little Conestoga Creek in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. A county-owned and maintained bridge, its official designation is the Little Conestoga #1 Bridge. Wikipedia

Lambeth Bridge.label: Lambeth Bridge
Lambeth Bridge.description: Lambeth Bridge is a road traffic and footbridge crossing the River Thames in an east-west direction in central London, the river flows north at the crossing point. Wikipedia

Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Br.label: Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Bridge
Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Br.description: The Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Bridge is a cable-stayed bridge across the Charles River in Boston, Massachusetts. It is a replacement for the Charlestown High Bridge, an older truss bridge constructed in the 1950s. Wikipedia

Keretapi Tanah Melayu.label: Keretapi Tanah Melayu
Keretapi Tanah Melayu.description: Keretapi Tanah Melayu Berhad or Malayan Railways Limited is the main rail operator in Peninsular Malaysia. The railway system dates back to the British colonial era, when it was first built to transport tin. Wikipedia

Kiev Metro.label: Kiev Metro
Kiev Metro.description: The Kiev Metro is a metro system that is the mainstay of Kiev's public transport. It was the first rapid transit system in Ukraine and the third one built in the USSR. It now has three lines with a total length of 66.6 kilometres and 52 stations. Wikipedia

Ländchesbahn.label: Ländches Railway
Ländchesbahn.description: The Ländches Railway is a single non-electrified branch railway line between Wiesbaden and Niedernhausen, Germany. The 19.6-kilometre long line was opened in July 1879 by the Hessian Ludwig Railway. Wikipedia

Lima Metro.label: Lima Metro
Lima Metro.description: The Lima Metro, colloquially referred to as El Tren Eléctrico by Lima residents, is a metropolitan railway currently linking south Lima with the centre of the capital of Peru. Wikipedia

Mühlviertler Schnellstraße.label: Mühlviertler Schnellstraße
Mühlviertler Schnellstraße.description: Mühlviertler Schnellstraße is an under construction schnellstraße in Austria. One 1,970-metre section of the Neumarkt tunnel is already in operation. Wikipedia

Lyublinsko-Dmitrovskaya Line.label: Lyublinsko-Dmitrovskaya Line
Lyublinsko-Dmitrovskaya Line.description: Lyublinsko-Dmitrovskaya Line is the line of the Moscow Metro. It was known as "Lyublinskaya Line" before 2007. First opened in 1995 as a semi-chordial radius it is at present in process of being extended through the centre and northwards. Wikipedia

M11 motorway.label: M11 motorway
M11 motorway.description: The M11 is a motorway in England running approximately north from the North Circular Road in South Woodford in northeast London to the A14, northwest of Cambridge. Wikipedia

M1 motorway (Northern Ireland).label: M1 motorway
M1 motorway (Northern Ireland).description: The M1 is a motorway in Northern Ireland. It is the longest motorway in Northern Ireland and runs for 38 miles from Belfast to Dungannon through County Down and County Armagh. Wikipedia

Mark Clark Bridge.label: Mark Clark Bridge
Mark Clark Bridge.description: The Mark Clark Bridge, built in 1949, carried Washington State Route 532 across the Stillaguamish River to connect Stanwood, Washington to Camano Island. It provided the only road access to the island. Wikipedia

M15 motorway (Hungary).label: M15 motorway
M15 motorway (Hungary).description: The M15 motorway is a Hungarian motorway connects the M1 motorway to Bratislava, the capital of Slovakia. The Hungary-Slovakia border crossing is at Rajka (Hungary) and Čunovo. Wikipedia

Mainzer Landstraße.label: Mainzer Landstraße
Mainzer Landstraße.description: Mainzer Landstraße is one of the main arterial roads in Frankfurt am Main, running west from the city centre to the outlying suburbs of the city. Wikipedia

Mariazell Railway.label: Mariazell Railway
Mariazell Railway.description: The Mariazell Railway is an electrically operated narrow-gauge railway which connects the Lower Austrian capital Sankt Pölten with the Styrian pilgrimage centre of Mariazell. Wikipedia

M7 motorway (Hungary).label: M7 motorway
M7 motorway (Hungary).description: The M7 motorway is a Hungarian motorway which runs from Budapest towards the Croatian border at Letenye, reaching Székesfehérvár, then Siófok, a town on Lake Balaton, and the city of Nagykanizsa in the southwest of the country. Wikipedia

Memphis Suspension Railway.label: Memphis Suspension Railway
Memphis Suspension Railway.description: The Memphis Suspension Railway or Mud Island Monorail is a suspended monorail that connects the city center of Memphis with the entertainment park on Mud Island. Wikipedia
